President Donald J. Trump visited the Royal Palace in Brussels to meet with King Philippe and Queen Mathilde and with Prime Minister Charles Michel of Belgium. During the visit, the President expressed appreciation for the hospitality and support for better economic relations between Belgium and the United States. They also discussed the centennial year of the Commission for Relief in Belgium, which supported Belgians during World War I and currently supports educational exchanges with the United States. In a meeting with Prime Minister Charles Michel, the President praised Belgian contributions to the Global Coalition to Counter ISIS and discussed the importance of all NATO members meeting defense spending commitments. The two leaders also discussed improving cooperation on counterterrorism and strengthening the economic and security relationship between the US and Europe.